SENATE JOINT RESOLUTION 819
By Stevens
A RESOLUTION to congratulate Hudson McDaniel of Dresden
High School on winning the 2025 TSSAA Class
A Girls' Cross Country Individual Championship.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to specially honor and
commend those successful high school athletes who, through their magnificent exploits, bring
honor to Tennessee and serve as exceptional ambassadors of this State; and
WHEREAS, one such estimable athlete is Hudson McDaniel of Dresden High School,
who won the 2025 TSSAA Class A Girls' Individual State Cross Country Championship held at
Shelby Farms Park in Memphis on November 6-7, 2025; and
WHEREAS, Ms. McDaniel's winning time of 19:12 secured the championship and
demonstrated her exceptional endurance, discipline, and competitive spirit; and
WHEREAS, a freshman at Dresden High School, Hudson McDaniel is noted for being
part of the first-ever duo (along with Vaughn Bounds) to win state titles for the school in the
same year; and
WHEREAS, a standout athlete, Ms. McDaniel was named to the 2025 All-West
Tennessee Team, further distinguishing herself as one of the premier competitors in the region;
and
WHEREAS, Hudson McDaniel's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of
pride for her family, her school, and her community; and
WHEREAS, Ms. McDaniel's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of our respect,
admiration, and commendation; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE OF THE ONE HUNDRED FOURTEENTH
GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE HOUSE OF
REPRESENTATIVES CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate Hudson McDaniel of
